<h1 class="full"><%= breadcrumbs :admin, :help %></h1>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">
  <a name="orders">Orders</a>
</h2>
<div class="third">
  <h4>Viewing all orders</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Orders', orders_path %> to view all orders. On this page, you can also
    click 'View processed' and 'View unprocessed' in the upper right corner to view those respective
    selections. When viewing all orders, the orders are positioned by date and the processed orders
    will appear in grey. To download a CSV file of the orders, click on the "Download CSV File"
    link at the bottom left of the page.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>Editing an order</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Orders', orders_path %> and find the order you wish to edit and click on the
    corresponding 'Edit' link. You can edit all fields and click on 'Update Order' to save changes.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>Viewing an order</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Orders', orders_path %> and find the order you wish to edit and click on the
    corresponding 'Show' link. All the order's information will be displayed along with the products
    that were purchased in the respective order. The button in the lower left will toggle the order
    to be either processed or unprocessed. The link next to the 'Mark as (not) processed' button will
    send a receipt of the order to the email specified in the order. If a customer has mistyped his or
    her email, one can edit the order's email and click 'Resend receipt' to send another receipt to
    the correct email.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">
  <a name="schools">Schools</a>
</h2>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create a school</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New School', new_school_path %>. Enter an appropriate title and leave
    slug blank for the system to automatically create one. Select multiple package types
    by holding down the 'Shift' key. These package types will be displayed for the school.
    Select a school type for the school to show up under. Check the 'Ask for teacher?' box
    if you want the website to ask for the student's teacher when ordering for this school.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit a school</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Schools', schools_path %>. Find the school you want
    to edit, and to the left, click 'Edit'. Follow the same directions in the
    'To create a school' section.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view a school</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Schools', schools_path %>. Find the school you want
    to view, and to the left, click 'Show'. All the school's information will
    be displayed.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">
  <a name="portrait_packages">Portrait Packages</a>
</h2>
<p class="full">
  Package types are logical groups of individual packages.
</p>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create a package type</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New Package Type' %>. Enter an appropriate title and leave slug blank
    to let the system automatically generate one. Check the 'Ask for sport level?' box if you
    want to ask the customer for sport level. Select multiple schools for which this package
    type will be available under by holding the 'Shift' key. You can also select multiple packages
    that will belong to this package type by holding the 'Shift' key. If you want an image to show
    for this package type, click 'Choose File' and pick an image.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit an package type</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Package Types', package_types_path %>. Find the package type you want
    to edit, and to the left, click 'Edit'. Follow the same directions in the
    'To create an package type' section.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view an package type</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Package Types', package_types_path %>. Find the package type you want
    to view, and to the left, click 'Show'. All the package type's information will
    be displayed.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>
<div class="two_thirds_box">
  <h4 class="half">To create a package</h4>
  <p class="third">
    Click on <%= link_to 'New Package', new_package_path %>.
    Add a title as a name for the package.
    Leave slug blank to let it automatically create one.
    Select a package type that the package will belong to
    Select multiple option types the customer will be able to
    choose by holding down the 'shift' key.
    Check the 'Email digital copy of the photo?' box if you want the
    customer to be sent an email with their photo. If this is checked,
    make sure the purchase id box is checked. The following two sections
    involve setting the price and what option types
  </p>
  <p class="third">
    are available to the customer. Setting a price and option type are not optional,
    but setting a school, begin date, and end date are optional. When a school is set,
    the price or option type will show up under that school. The price and option
    types will only show up after the begin date and before the end date.
    When they are not set, the price or option type will show up indefinitely.
    To delete a price or option type from showing up, check the 'Destroy?' box
    and click 'Update Package'. To add an image for a package, click 'Choose File'
    under the 'Image' section and choose an appropriate file.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit a package</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Packages', packages_path %>. Find the package you want
    to edit, and to the left, click 'Edit'. Follow the same directions in the
    'To create a package' section.
  </p>
  <h4>To view a package</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Packages', packages_path %>. Find the package you want
    to view, and to the left, click 'Show'. All the package's information will
    be displayed.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">
  <a name="options">Options</a>
</h2>
<p class="full">
  Option types are logical groups of individual options.
</p>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create an option type</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New Option Type', new_option_type_path %>.
    Enter an appropriate title, select the packages for which this set of options is availble for. And finally select
    the options that will be grouped in this option set. The section below contains the options for which schools and
    for which times option sets are available. To set these, you must select all the schools you want to apply in the top
    section and then click 'Create Option Type' and then click 'Edit' at the bottom of the next page.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit an option type</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Option Types', option_types_path %>. Find the option type you want
    to edit, and to the left, click 'Edit'. Follow the same directions in the
    'To create an option type' section.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view an option type</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Option Types', option_types_path %>. Find the option type you want
    to view, and to the left, click 'Show'. All the option type's information will
    be displayed.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="clear"></div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create an option</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New Option', new_option_path %>. Enter an appropriate title and select an option type for which
    it will belong to. Optionally, click 'Choose File' and pick a file that visually describes the option. Below is the price
    section. If school, begin, and end are left blank, the price will apply to all schools all the time. When a school is chosen,
    the price will only apply to that school. The begin and end fields act similarly. To add another price field, click 'Update
    Option' and click 'Edit' on the following page.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit an option</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Options', options_path %>. Find the option you want
    to edit, and to the left, click 'Edit'. Follow the same directions in the
    'To create an option' section.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view an option</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Options', options_path %>. Find the option you want
    to view, and to the left, click 'Show'. All the option's information will
    be displayed.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">
  <a name="print_products">Print Products</a>
</h2>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create a product</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New Product', new_product_path %>. Enter an appropriate title and leave slug blank for the system
    to automatically generate one. Enter a price and a minimum quantity. Prices may have decimals, quantities should not. Click
    on 'Choose File' to pick an image for this product.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit an product</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'products', products_path %>. Find the product you want
    to edit, and to the left, click 'Edit'. Follow the same directions in the
    'To create an product' section.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view an product</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'products', products_path %>. Find the product you want
    to view, and to the left, click 'Show'. All the product's information will
    be displayed.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">Pages</h2>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create a page</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New Page', new_page_path %>. Enter an appropriate title and leave slug blank to let the system automatically
    create one. Select a parent page if you want this page to belong to another. In the body, enter html and text.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit a page</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Pages', pages_path %>. Find the page you wish to edit and click the corresponding 'Edit' link. The instructions
    are similar to the ones listed under 'To create a page'.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view a page</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Pages', pages_path %>. Find the page you wish to view and click the corresponding 'Show' link. The page will
    be shown as it would be seen by a user.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">Navigation</h2>
<p class="full">Navigation links are sometimes listed as 'Nav Links'.</p>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create a navigation link</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New Navigation Link', new_nav_link_path %>. Enter an appropriate title. In the slug field, enter the url
    for the corresponding page for this link. Select a parent navigation link if you want the link to belong to another link. Select a
    position for the link, which the links are ordered by relative to each other.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit a navigation link</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Navigation Links', nav_links_path %>. Find the link you want to edit and click 'Edit' next to it. Follow the
    same instructions as listed in 'To create a navigation link'.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view a navigation link</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Navigation Links', nav_links_path %>. Find the link you want to view and click 'Show' next to it. All the
    information about the link will be listed there.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">Users</h2>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To create a user</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'New User', new_user_path %>. Enter a login, email, password, and password confirmation and select multiple roles
    for this user to have by holding the 'Shift' key. The 'admin' role can edit and view all aspects of the website so user with caution.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To edit a user</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Users', users_path %>. Find the user you wish to edit and click 'Edit' next to it. Follow the instructions under
    'To create a user'.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To view a user</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Users', users_path %>. Find the user you wish to view and click 'view' next to it. All the information regarding
    the selected user will be listed on this page.
  </p>
</div>
<hr class="full" />
<h2 class="full">Mass Emailer</h2>
<div class="third">
  <h4>To send emails to many people</h4>
  <p>
    Click on <%= link_to 'Emailer', mailer_path %>. In the 'Addresses' box, type in the email addresses, each on a separate line. Type an appropriate
    title. Enter your message in the 'Message' box, which can include HTML. Click 'Start Sending' button to begin. Do not close the window until
    you get an alert saying the batch is complete.
  </p>
</div>